2. THE SOCIAL CONTRACT (PLAIN ENGLISH SUMMARY)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
This software is an instrument of sovereign infrastructure. It is free to
use, but it is not without cost. The cost is reciprocity.

THE ENGINE (LCL-1.0):
   The compiler and its core tools are licensed under LCL-1.0.
   If you modify OR run these tools as a service (SaaS),
   you MUST share those modifications back with the commonwealth.

THE MODULES (LSL-1.0):
   The standard libraries and runtime are licensed under LSL-1.0.
   You are free to link these into proprietary applications ("Larger Works").
   We do not require you to open-source your own logic, but changes
   to the modules themselves must be shared.

THE COMMONS (LUL-1.0):
   Examples, tests, and documentation are licensed under LUL-1.0.
   Maximum freedom for learning, teaching, and peripheral tooling.

THE BRAND (The Shield):
   You have a license to the code, NOT the identity.
   You may NOT use the names "Self Sovereign Society," "Janus Core," or
   associated Foundation logos to endorse or promote your derived products
   without written permission.

   If you fork this, you must distinguish it.
   Do not confuse the market.

3. PATENT GRANT & TERMINATION
